documents.title: Tim Berners-Lee Biography
documents.content: Sir Timothy John Berners-Lee, known as Tim Berners-Lee, is an English computer scientist best known as the inventor of the World Wide Web. He made a proposal for an information management system in March 1989, and he implemented the first successful communication between a Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) client and server via the Internet in mid-November 1989.
